<br>
Yes, this is long and has been edited for the main thrust of the story. Any section not marked with an author was done by me.<br>
<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Darkmask enters the Missed Note early in the morning, when the dew was still fresh on the grass in the commonlands, not a beast was stirring, only Harte was quietly working behind the bar arranging bottles for the day.<br>
&quot; Hail Harte Greyeagle &quot; Darkmask said with a grain to his voice. Darkmask digs into his backpack removing a key to a room above, and lays on the bar, &quot; I need to return this to you, I wont be needing it, I wont be staying here any longer, it is time for me to go &quot; <br>
Harte looked up at the High Elf whose eyes were bloodshot, and tears streamed down his face, Harte spook with confidence as he said &quot; Well dont be silly Darkmask, you can hold the key for when you get back, I wont rent out your room &quot;<br>
&quot; You dont understand &quot; Darkmask said &quot; I am not coming back, ever &quot; and he pushed the key with one finger towards Harte, who looked up at the enchanter, and raised his eyebrows in a concerned manner. Harte spoke softly and said &quot; Do you need to talk about anything..anything at all, I am here for you, here let me get you a drink, we should talk &quot;<br>
Darkmask stiffened &quot; No &quot; and looked the half elf in his green eyes &quot; I am done, finished, my heart is turned cold, my soul has rotted, I am burnt within &quot;<br>
&quot; Darkmask, we not have always agreed on things, but I wouldnt want to see you leave, neither would many of our regulars, alot of people have come to expect you and look forward to seeing you &quot; Harte with as much heartful compassion he could find.<br>
&quot; Its too late Harte, its too late, when you cry everytime you enter Norrath, and you feel that all the goodness that once swept beneath your feet when you walked has been sucked out, that all that joy you had, is gone, all you have come to know has slipped through your fingertips, it is time to slip with it, Harte I am not well, my heart is weak, I am going away....away to die in peace, away from the crowded tavern, away from the notions of hateful people, away from it all, I want the world to be silent the day I die, nothing can stop this...noone can stop this &quot;<br>
Harte dropped his bar rag, and almost dropped the bottle of elven wine &quot; I....I....I dont know what to say &quot; as Darkmask picked the key up, and placed it on the rack behind him.<br>
&quot; Say nothing, I want to be alone, I have to be.... &quot; Darkmask said as he turned his head, and walked out the Note, sliding his hand down the door, in a moment of memories, all the times, all the people, he remembered it all, he would take it with him, but now, now he must go.<br>
&quot; Harte, just if they ask about me, tell them I love them, I really do, I carry them with me &quot; Darkmask said as he touched his heart, and vanished in bubbles of light....... <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Harte stared at the spot where Darkmask had stood for a long time. It seems that Darkmask preferred the place a little quieter, maybe he longed for the days when there were very few people who visited the Note each day.<br>
Harte was certain that Darkmask wasn't longing for the days when outsiders came to the Inn and attacked Sasi's character.... that certainly wasn't fun.<br>
Harte felt sure that Darkmask didn't miss the days when the Note seemed to get burned down constantly or when everyone who came near it seemed to die.<br>
What Harte did know is that Darkmask missed Sasi. But she is still here, in the Note. Her spirit is obvious in the many stories told throughout the day, her instruments are still sitting right where she left them and most of her friends are still visiting regularly. Harte fully expected her to be back.<br>
Harte wondered where else Darkmask will find the feeling that can be found only at the Missed Note? <br>
Harte Greyeagle<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Harte stood there staring and contemplating all that went on, all of it, and how Darkmask will be missed and wondered exactly he meant by dying...what was wrong he thought.....suddenly Hartes senses which were more keen then the average man smelled wild lillies breath into the room and the front door to the Note opened once again, last being closed by Darkmask, Harte looked up expecting Darkmask, but smelling the scent of a women, he was none too susprised at seeing a cloaked female figure enter with the hood over her face, as she came in, her hands went to hood and removing it, Harte was stunned, this woman was the most beautiful high elf he had ever seen, her skin was so soft looking, her lips so tempting, her eyes a deep topaz blue which Harte seemed to gaze at, her thin blonde hair swept over her face, she had high beautiful cheekbones, which were colored with a natural rosy blush, and she smiled at Harte.<br>
&quot; Sir &quot; She said &quot; I am looking for Sasi Greyeagle, I was told she could direct me to my husband Darkmask Disillusion &quot; Harte's jaw seemed to seperate from his skull entirely as he thought it hit the floor.<br>
&quot; Excuse me? &quot; He said with an odd confused expression.<br>
&quot; My husband, the enchanter Darkmask, I have come to find him and bring him home &quot; she said as she removed pristine white gloves, and walked towards Harte at the bar.... <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------As Harte found his tongue, he stumbled over his words..<br>
&quot;D.. duh.... darkmask! Ahh yes, my... my lady. He has been here at the Missed Note for quite sometime. Unfortunately, I muh... must tell you that today, just this morning actually, he came to turn in his key and spoke of leaving the Note permanently.&quot;<br>
When Harte saw the look of disappointment on the High elf's fine features, he could actually feel her pain.<br>
&quot;Well my lady, some of the patrons did go after him to attempt to bring him back. You are welcome to wait here for him, for as long as you wish. Here is the key that he returned to me, you can have his room. Can I get you something to eat? to drink?&quot;<br>
Harte could not imagine how this turn of events occurred, but his curiosity was piqued.<br>
Harte Greyeagle<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Harte was scanning the high elf, she was something to behold, glorius, all religious in her very presence, like she had been blessed with Tunare's soul, and Harte could feel it, he noticed the fine clothes she wore, the fines silks, she was most definately royalty, you could tell by the clothes and the way she carried herself, and the way she walked, you never saw her robe move, it was like she glided across the floor.<br>
She had turned from Harte at his response and surveyed the tavern, it was still morning and and not a patron was the downstairs. Her eyes seemed to float around the room looking at every detail, she was intesely scanning it all, and her eyes stopped at a knife sunk into overhang above the bar, her eyes floated back to Harte who had been following her every move with his eyes, he was fasincated by her, she was like an event the he couldnt take his off eyes off of. She sighed, to which Harte said &quot; Anything I can get you, I can make some eggs, or some toast, or do you want something to drink? &quot;<br>
She seemed to ignore his voice, but down the steps came a half dressed Ninou wearing nothing but a light white silk robe, Ninou not noticing the robe was open as she descended the steps and she beamed a smile at Harte who blushed suddenly. He wasnt a stranger to beautiful women, but one so sure of herself as Ninou and not embarrassed by anything always struck him as odd, but he liked her strength. The High Elven Woman looked at Ninou as she came down, and High Elven Woman looked at Harte and said &quot; I see, this is a whore house.... &quot; as the High Elf looked right back at Ninou as she was lifting a cup of warm coffee to her lips. Ninou's eye raised at the remark &quot; It is now, we were all out of whores until you walked in... &quot; Ninou shot back with smile as she turned and let the robe fall down to her shoulders as she proceeded back upstairs. The High Elven woman seemed to choke on the comment, taken aback by such brazen words and she retorted &quot; I would expect no less of a mouth on a dark skinned slave woman &quot; That comment seemed to hit Ninou, but she smirked and said &quot; You should expect more of a mouth on me, and if you are intrested come up to my room and I can show you. &quot; to which the end of her white robe vanished past the top of the steps.<br>
The High Elven Woman smirked and looked at Harte &quot; You let that type of mouthy woman in this place? &quot; Harte caught up in the moment of Ninou's quips lost control and said &quot; Yeah, we do, but I am regretting letting you in though... &quot;<br>
&quot; Why I never.. &quot; She flustered back.<br>
&quot; Aye it shows &quot; Harte bit his tounge as he knew he was being unkind, he liked the feeling, but knew it wasnt him. He heard a little giggle from upstairs at his last comment and blushed knowing he crossed the line of a host.<br>
&quot; I am sorry My'Lady &quot; Harte said apologetically as he poured her a cup of warm black coffee and reached out with it in hand towards her. &quot; Please have a seat, Vandaal will be up soon and will help me make some breakfast, I am sure you would feel better after you ate. &quot; <br>
&quot; Is Sasi Greyeagle here or coming soon &quot; in a disappointed and hopeful voice the High Elven Woman asked again.<br>
&quot; Well she is away and I am in charge &quot; Harte said as a crowd of High Elves walked in, some in armor and some in robes, all seemed to be in Royal Armor.<br>
&quot; Princess Larenina!! thank Tunare!! &quot; said one of the older High Elves in robes as he ran to the Woman at the table with Harte and kneeled.<br>
Harte's eyebrows twisted as the confusion this morning had seemed to reach its pinacle.<br>
The High Elves in Armor seemed to set themselves up at vital areas in the Note, establishing a defense. <br>
&quot; Hath thee found Lord Chel~ ? &quot; The old high elf in well decorated robes asked of the Princess.<br>
&quot; Chel~ ? &quot; Harte asked &quot; I thought you were looking for Darkmask? &quot;<br>
&quot; Indeed, Indeed one in the same, Darkmask is the name he seems to have adopted when he left the palace &quot; The old high elf said to Harte.<br>
&quot; Silence!! &quot; the Princess stood up &quot; Speak not for me Vernale! I am the Princess of the Sixth House and do not need others to speak for me, let alone to half elves! &quot; as she turned and headed towards the door &quot; Silent Watch go get the things from my husbands room! &quot; she tossed the key towards one of the guards who seemed like stone until the key was right in front of him and then his hand shot out, grabbed the key and shot back to his side, if Harte didnt pay attention he could of swore the High Elf didnt move. <br>
&quot; We are staying at a decent hotel, not a country inn, lets be off &quot; The Princess motioned as the crowded swirled around her and vanished out the door, followed by two high elves carrying five large chests as if they were weightless. Harte was a little taken aback by all this, but he threw the rag over his shoulder and walked back towards the bar.<br>
Vandaal was bouncing down the steps ready and eager to work &quot; Morning Harte! how is it going? &quot;<br>
&quot; Confusing, very confusing &quot; Harte shot back puzzled as he walked passed the swinging door into the kitchen...... <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Ninou dressed slowly,while standing in front of the window. She watched as the High Elven woman strolled out of the Note in a hurry. As the woman glanced up at the window Ninou blew her a kiss and struck a provactive pose. Then she left the view of the window and finished putting on her armor. The day was hot,already sweat glistened on her dark skin. Not caring for the banded armor she normally wore she had pulled on the leather again. Grinning she winked at her reflection,loving the way the leather looked. Her tunic;well you couldnt really call it a tunic,it was just some leather straps crossed over her breasts,left hardly anything to the imagination. She was in a very playful mood today,no nightmares had tormented her through the night. Besides,she didnt kill a man yesterday....this day would be good. Once again her thoughts strayed to Darkmask,wondering where the enchanter was...how he was doing.<br>
Frowning she shook her head and attached her cleaver to her belt. As she came down the stairs,she flashed Harte a dazzling smile. One that truly lit up her face,she giggled and leaned across the counter. &quot;So,who was M'Lady Goody Goody and her half-wit drones?&quot; She asked throwing a wink his way.<br>
Harte smiled at the wink but then his brow wrinkled in confusion,&quot;Said her name was Princess Larenina,&quot; Harte's green eyes eyed Ninou for a moment before he continued to speak. &quot;Darkmask's wife.&quot;<br>
Ninou sat up and raised her eyebrows,&quot;Wife?&quot; She frowned,&quot;I didnt know the Ol' High Elf was married,more or less to a Princess.&quot; She slightly frowned her eyes drifting off in thought. Then shaking her head as if trying to get rid of her thoughts she once again smiled the rare smile. &quot;So handsome,I guess I'm the last remaining Barmaid?&quot; <br>
Harte nodded and handed her a tray,a smile tugging at his mouth as she groaned taking it. He was silent this morning,as if his thoughts too were clouded around something out of his grasp. Ninou leaned forward and let her lips brush his cheek. &quot;Get your head out of the gutter man,oh and Harte?&quot; He turned to look at her his hand placed where her lips had been. Ninou grinned,her bright green eyes twinkling,&quot;Hope you liked my robe!&quot; She winked and walked away her hips moving teasingly as she walked.....<br>
Ninou<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Harte chuckled as Ninou walked away to tend the tables.<br>
He enjoyed the game and a little bit of flirting was always fun, but to ever fall for one so bent on working her charms for attention he knew to be a huge mistake. Harte preferred a more sensitive woman, one that would only have eyes for him and leave no man, friend or foe, ever considering an opportunity to take her from him.<br>
He enjoyed watching Ninou work the men and even more so, he laughed at how the men all fell for it. Harte would keep both Mye and Ninou as barmaids for as long as they'd stay, for they surely added to the Note. <br>
For him, there must be someone, something more. <br>
Harte Greyeagle<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Ninou wiped the sweat from her forhead and glanced around the busy tavern. Since Mye had left to find her husband she was stuck with all the work. Frowning she plucked up a shot glass from her tray and downed it. The warm sting made her sigh. She missed the old days when she would get sloshed out of her mind.....it had been awhile. Picking up another she finished it off then continued her rounds. By the end of the evening she had a glazed look in her eyes and she had become more flirtatous then usual. Her giggles echoing through the Note as she passed out drinks,once in awhile taking a drink of her own. Once the Note had settled down some she leaned against the bar. Barely able to hold her own self up...few noticed her condition. Mostly the men who grinned at each other,and whispeared to each other. Ninou laughed and sighed,she glanced at the dwindling people and tried to sit on a bar stool. Her balence off from the many drinks she had,she couldnt stay on the stool. Giggling she shruged to herself and leaned against the counter again. <br>
Out of no where a shiver ran up her spine as if she was being watched....her cat like eyes darted back and forth. <br>
Ninou<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------She watched as the Shadow Knight drunk herself to a stupor. Finding it hard to not gigle out loud along with the drunk woman. Her invisabilty allowed her to move freely along the Tavern,without being noticed. When finally Ninou returned to her drinking she moved closer to the bar. Her dark eyes sizing up the woman,and frowning. <br>
Ninou grabbed one more shot glass and tilted it up,then without notice she passed out on the bar. <br>
The Erudite Enchantress laughed silently and shook Ninou's shoulder to get her moving. Once the woman was to her feet,she helped her up the stairs to her room. Making sure Ninou was carefully tucked in bed,she left the room and said a silent prayer for the woman to rest peacfully.<br>
Coming back down the stairs she waited till the bartender turned his back and took one of the room keys from the shelf and left a gold peice on the bar. Then heading to the room she had just silently purchased for the night she unlocked the door and relocked it. Once saftly in the room she dropped her invisablity and dropped her packs on the floor near the bed. Pulling off the robe she climbed under the covers and said softly to herself,&quot;Tomorrow be along day,that be the truth!&quot; she drifted off into sleep....<br>
Maxima<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Ninou stirred in the bed and blinked open her blurry eyes....<br>
&quot;How the hell did I get up here?&quot;<br>
She climbed out of the bed on unsteady legs. Hic-uping hse giggled and left the room...she was not going to bed just yet....<br>
Bouncing down the stairs she surveyed the remaining men in the tavern. A grin came to her face as she held onto the door way for suport. She winked at a table,she couldnt tell if they were locals or not....her vision was blurred. She didnt care either,a thought pulled at her mind...something familar. A feeling that she was no longer alone this night. &quot;Hmm....&quot;she giggled to herself,&quot;Whos the lucky guy?&quot; a loud hic-up escaped her mouth and she busted out laughing. Covering her mouth with her finger she whispeared to no one in particular,&quot;Shhh&quot;<br>
Then straightening up she put a hand on her hip and proceded to walk towards the bar. Her bright green eyes took on a new look.....the look of a cat hunting her prey.<br>
Ninou<br>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
As Ninou was enjoying the drink tad too much, a rather large gentleman entered the Note, his arms were large and thick, and brow furrowed, he had the look of a warrior, and you could see all the scars and scratches on his arms, his armor was heavily dented but it could be seen that it was armor from the planes, the brown texture be no other, on his back was strapped a massive sword, and he seemed to be unaware of anything happening in the bar.<br>
Ninou staggered over to the rather large man, and she fingered his bulging arms and then patted them saying &quot; Oh so firm &quot; and the large man looked down at her and she grinned &quot; I wonder if yer the lucky one to have a taste of Ninou tonight &quot; <br>
In a gruff tone he replied &quot; I am not hungry tonight, maybe some other time &quot; To which Ninou's lips form quite a little pouting frown. He looked at her and asked &quot; Have you seen Lord Darkmask this day? &quot;<br>
&quot; My my he has become quite popular, some high elf woman wanted him too, said she was his wife ( Hiccup ) &quot; Ninou stammered back.<br>
&quot; Oh Karana! I am too late, she has come for him! &quot; He cupped his forehead. &quot; Did she take him? &quot;<br>
&quot; Goodness no, he left this morn and hasnt been seen since, come, lets go to my room and see if we can find him ( Hiccup ), he might be hiding under my sheets, lets go look! &quot; Ninou smiled, the drink had filled her head and loosened her tounge.<br>
&quot; No time woman, I need to find him, do know what direction he took off into, or where he was headed, I need to find him before she does or all is lost! &quot;<br>
&quot; I told you he's hiding under my sheets, come ( drool ) upstai ( BAM )&quot; Ninou's head slamed into the table, passed out cold.<br>
&quot; Dammit! &quot; and he got up and left the note running off towards freeport. <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Vandaal turned towards the sound of Ninou's head hitting the table as she plunged into unconsciousness. I'm going to have to start charging her for drinks if she's going to get that stewed he thought to himself. As he walked over to where she sat with her head on the table, the large man she had been speaking with turned to him.<br>
He asked the direction that Darkmask had headed when he left, as well as several other questions Vandaal could not answer. Unsure whether this man was friend or foe to Darkmask, Vandaal kept a tight lip, insisting that he did not know where Darkmask had gone. The large man became increasingly agitated until Vandaal told him that he would be best off talking to Harte about it, as he would know better than most where Darkmask had set out for. This seemed to satisfy the large warrior to some extent, for he sat at a nearby table and waited, constantly fidgeting, as Vandaal headed in Harte's direction.<br>
From across the room, the large man saw Vandaal approach Harte and speak softly to him. Twice he pointed at him. As Harte headed back towards the large warrior, Vandaal headed quickly up the back stairs in search of some of the heartier warriors who frequented the Note, preparing for the worst.<br>
Vandaal <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
After a few moments,Ninou raised her head again. Rubbing her pounding temples,she blinked her eyes and glanced around. Sighing she started to rise but dizzness took her and she thought it best to stay seated. She hadnt drank this much in a long time,a slight smile tugged at the corners of her mouth. She was rather surprised she was still alone for the night. <br>
&quot;Hmm....&quot;She looked around at the last remaining people. Her eyes noticed the Warrior again,frowning she made a Tisk,Tisk sound and shook her head. &quot;No one to play with me tonight..how boring.&quot; Slowly she stood,her legs numb from the drink. &quot;Maybe...I better go to bed....alone.&quot;She breathed leaning against the counter as she walked to the stairwell.<br>
Half way up the stairs she scratched her head and took off her helmet,letting it roll back down the stairs. After a few more steps her boots were off...wiggling her toes she smiled. &quot;Much better,&quot;Leaving her boots on the stairs,&quot;I'll get them in the morning.&quot; Giggling loudly she blew a kiss at a woman coming down the stairs. Gasping the woman frowned and turned her eyes away. Ninou grinnned and shrugged,&quot;Just trying to have alittle fun darlin...&quot; she said to herself....<br>
Stopping to rest at the top of the stairs ninou held her dizzy head in her hands. &quot;Gods....all the blasted spinning!&quot; Looking at the numbers on the doors she stumbled backwards....almost falling down the stairs. Catching herself,she staggered forward,&quot;hmm..that would not have been good! (Hic-up)&quot;She giggled again. Door number 3 was open,Ninou peeked in...her eyes looking around. &quot;Hey..your door's open....better close it..too many (Hic-up) strange people out here!&quot;She shouted,then walked on to her room.<br>
At her room,she opened the door and almost fell in. Laughing she shook her head making the Tisk Tisk noise again. Forgetting to close the door,she stripped down and walked to the window. Darkness had settled through out the Commons. She could see a few people,out side of the door. Resting in the cool air of the night. Ninou sighed and stretched,her muscles flexing. Her dark skin gleamed in the lamp's light. Turning she climbed into her bed and put out the lamp. It didnt take long before she was sleeping peacfully. No dreams would wake her tonight......she was out cold. <br>
Ninou<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
The campfire popped and the wood in it hissed as the small amount of water left in the wood was being seared out, it was going to be a cold night in the mountains, the wind was already whispering Karanas lullaby ( comes from an old childhood ledgend that Karana, god of the storm would sing children to sleep with a soothing wind )and the High Elf enchanter punched his pack to soften it for his head, that not doing the trick his proceeded to bang it several times on the ground....the pack, not his head. <br>
Darkmask felt the tremor in his heart, he knew his time was fast approaching when Karana would sweep his soul back into the wind. Darkmask layed down and let his eyes slide shut. As the eyelids collided over his weary eyes, images flashed in his head, all he had seen, all he felt now, the madness stirring within, the pain of his heart, all the sins of his past, he clutched his fists to his chest. His mind raced and he thought of love, all it meant to him, the past raced in front of him and he saw all the mistakes he had made, the woman he had not fought to hold on, but instead abandoned her. He was in love with....... <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Darkmask whispered the name of his true love into Karana's wind, and it lifted as the sound of the breeze took it higher and higher into the air, like the name had become a life of its own, Darkmask's eyes shut tight, his heart slowed, his pulse started falter, and he could feel the warmth drain from his body....this was his time, his god had come to take him......<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Back at the Note the two erudite sisters were disscussing matters at one of the tables, Ninou looked none too happy and Maxima just grinned like all Ninou was saying was funny as an Ogre swan diving into a river. The crowd at the note was filtering slowly but surely, and an odd figure walked in, his hood over his head, he slipped to the back corner table.<br>
Suddenly in came old Drezenal the drunken minstrel screaming about the high elf lady coming back to the note.<br>
&quot; Shes coming, and she looks angry! &quot; and he faltered threw the door. He was pushed out of the way by a high elf gaurd wearing shiney blue armor, and carrying a flaming sword, most of the people at the note recognized a soulfire, but this, this was the firey avenger, the sword of legend, the sword that only the most noble, the bravest, the most true of heart palidan may weild. And into the door came several of these guards all dressed in blue armor weilding firey avengers, it was a sight to behold, most of the patrons hadnt a clue what to do.<br>
