What Darkmask did with the children and where he fled Larenina will never know, but she knows, that Darkmask's name had been cleared by her son some years later, and that she was too prove that she was the rightful owner of the house ( which she had let go to waste ) and the money ( which she had spent most of it ), she was to return the family artifact, if she did, that would be a clear sign that Darkmask had given her control, but if she didnt return it with in a years time, she would be banished, and removed from the house, and her position of power taken away, her influnence and ties no more, and her private security, the silent watch, would be sent to another house. She would not lose all this, she had worked too hard, pulled too many strings to let her dear husband and his motherless son take it from her!! <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Dorraxx saw that Harte was doing his best to prepare for the journey and to gather those who would go, but the Dwarf also saw that Harte was deeply distracted, so he pitched in where he could.<br>
The supplies were easy enough to gather anyway. Harte was far more experienced than he at preparing for what they were to do, so Dorraxx left the Druid to those matters.<br>
Dorraxx found himself distracted at times, but it was the sisters Ninou and Maxima that provided his distraction. He liked Ninou. Something about the tragic young Shadow Knight drew him like a moth to the flame. He did not hold the fact that she was a fallen Paladin against her, indeed, he respected her even more for knowing herself enough to make the change. Many times he had seen Paladins across Norrath that were no better than Lucan himself. Ninou had more good in her than she believed, he saw it. Someday, perhaps she would too.<br>
Dorraxx's interest in other people had grown since he first traveled to Freeport many seasons before. While many of his race were content to stay in their Hold their whole lives, he had traveled the lands as soon as he could wield sword and shield. He enjoyed watching people and their interactions with each other and the world around them, and the tragic souls were the ones who always seemed to act with the most passion and intensity. Ninou was the most passionate and intense young woman he had met since - in a long while.<br>
Maxima was a different matter. Though appearing quite mad on the outside, her own intensity and clarity proved her to be anything but. She knew herself and and she had a gift for knowing the heart of those around her, all the while enjoying herself immensely at what ever task presently occupied her. She loved her sister, Dorraxx could tell, even though that love seemed to drive Ninou crazy at times.<br>
He chuckled to himself, drawing strange looks from a nearby table of patrons. Maxima would be Ninou's rock in the storm...and whether Ninou clung tightly to that rock or dashed herself upon it remained to be seen. <br>
Dorraxx<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------There at the bottom of the pit layed Darkmask, his head opened on a rock, the blood of his body pouring forth onto the ground, his skin had turned almost see through, the parts of his skin on the ground were deep purple though, he strained to breathe, the blood in his mouth filled, his body was broken through and through, his mind slowly drifted to a quiet place where he could be alone from all the pain....he found it, a golden light called to him, and he followed, as his mind was lost to the world, his heart slowly stopped pumping the blood onto the rocks....his breathing came to halt....Darkmask has died, alone, at the bottom of a cave.<br>
Soon goblins came, they saw the body, they smelled the flesh and blood, and they saw this as a treasure, they dragged the body to the underground city, there, they proceeded to slice and dice the enchanter like a fine piece of meat, each took turns tasting his flesh, goblins loved elven flesh, especially high elven flesh. They ate what was left of his body, and distrubuted the bones among the bonecasters and rockcharmers, the skull however was given to the cheif and he was to deliver it to Sathir's treasury.<br>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
What has become of Darkmask's Skull, no one yet knows, but it is rumored recently that only a vicar with divine powers can ressurect a body from shattered fragments. The soul is a different matter, his soul has gone to another plane, only with hope that he fell in love and gave his soul to someone, if so, the person he loves must take the piece in herself and place it back into his body during the cermony.<br>
<br>
